{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849283239,"sessionID":"ses_28722a5a2ffeY5t3bH1W5LyxEo","part":{"id":"prt_d78dd99750014is5ot3MnmzOgV","messageID":"msg_d78dd84da001BVFahffAoIlBAA","sessionID":"ses_28722a5a2ffeY5t3bH1W5LyxEo","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_87f0686cb2ae469d8cd10195","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement session management capabilities in `pkg/router` to track, manage, and persist user sessions when routing to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends. This enables sticky sessions, session affinity, session lifecycle management, and provides operational visibility into active sessions.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The AR-009 router implements HTTP reverse proxying to dynamically route requests to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter sandboxes. Currently:\n12: \n13: - **No session tracking**: Requests are routed without awareness of session context\n14: - **No sticky sessions**: Load balancing distributes requests across backends without session affinity\n15: - **No session lifecycle**: No mechanism to track when sessions start/end\n16: - **No session state visibility**: No way to query active sessions or session metadata\n17: \n18: ### Goal\n19: \n20: Provide session management that:\n21: - Tracks active sessions with unique identifiers\n22: - Supports sticky sessions (session affinity based on session ID)\n23: - Manages session lifecycle (creation, expiration, cleanup)\n24: - Provides session metadata storage (user ID, backend, start time, last activity)\n25: - Enables session-based access control\n26: - Exports session metrics for monitoring\n27: \n28: ### Value\n29: - Enables consistent user experience with sticky sessions\n30: - Provides audit trail for session activity\n31: - Supports session-based rate limiting per user\n32: - Enables session expiration for resource management\n33: - Improves operational visibility\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Scope\n38: \n39: ### In-Scope\n40: \n41: | Deliverable | Description |\n42: |-------------|-------------|\n43: | Session Store | In-memory store for session tracking with thread-safe operations |\n44: | Session ID Generation | Generate unique session IDs (UUID or similar) |\n45: | Session Affinity | Route requests to the same backend based on session cookie/header |\n46: | Session Lifecycle | Create, update, expire, and delete sessions |\n47: | Session Middleware | HTTP middleware to extract/inject session ID |\n48: | Session Metrics | Track active sessions, session rates, expirations |\n49: | Session Configuration | Configurable session timeout, cookie name, storage options |\n50: | Unit Tests | Core session logic coverage >70% |\n51: \n52: ### Code Structure\n53: \n54: ```\n55: pkg/router/\n56: ├── session/\n57: │   ├── session.go           # Session struct and interface\n58: │   ├── store.go             # Session store implementation\n59: │   ├── manager.go           # Session lifecycle manager\n60: │   └── config.go            # Session configuration\n61: ├── middleware/\n62: │   └── session.go           # Session middleware for HTTP\n63: └── (existing files...)\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ### Configuration\n67: \n68: The router supports these new session configuration options:\n69: \n70: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n71: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n72: | SessionEnabled | bool | false | Enable session management |\n73: | SessionTimeout | duration | 30m | Session expiration time |\n74: | SessionCookieName | string | \"AGENTSESSIONID\" | Cookie/header name for session ID |\n75: | SessionCookieDomain | string | \"\" | Cookie domain (empty = current domain) |\n76: | SessionCookieSecure | bool | true | Set Secure flag on cookie |\n77: | SessionCookieHTTPOnly | bool | true | Set HttpOnly flag on cookie |\n78: | SessionMaxActive | int | 10000 | Max concurrent sessions |\n79: | SessionCleanupInterval | duration | 5m | Interval for expired session cleanup |\n80: \n81: ### Out-of-Scope\n82: - Distributed session store (Redis, etcd) — future enhancement\n83: - Session persistence to Kubernetes CRD — future enhancement\n84: - Session replication across router instances\n85: - OIDC/OAuth2 session integration (use existing auth middleware)\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Impact Analysis\n90: \n91: ### Dependencies\n92: \n93: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n94: |------------|--------|---------|\n95: | github.com/google/uuid | ^1.6 | Session ID generation |\n96: | github.com/volcano/sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | local | CR types for session correlation |\n97: | github.com/volcano/sh/agentcube/pkg/router | local | Existing router module |\n98: \n99: ### Upstream Dependencies\n100: \n101: - **AR-009 Router Core** — Provides the reverse proxy foundation\n102: - **AR-007 K8s Reconciler** — Creates backends that sessions connect to\n103: \n104: ### Downstream Consumers\n105: \n106: 1. **External Clients** — Benefit from sticky sessions and consistent experience\n107: 2. **Monitoring Systems** — Session metrics for operational visibility\n108: 3. **Auth System** — Session-based access control integration\n109: \n110: ### Risks\n111: \n112: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n113: |------|----------|------------|\n114: | Memory exhaustion | Medium | Max session limit, automatic cleanup |\n115: | Session hijacking | Medium | Secure cookies, server-side session storage |\n116: | Session race conditions | Low | Thread-safe store implementation |\n117: | Cookie manipulation | Medium | Validate session ID format, server-side lookup |\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## Alternatives Considered\n122: \n123: ### Option 1: Cookie-Based Session with Backend Affinity (Selected)\n124: \n125: **Approach**: Use HTTP cookies to track session ID, route to the same backend based on session mapping.\n126: \n127: **Pros**:\n128: - Simple client integration (browser handles cookies)\n129: - Works with existing routing layer\n130: - Low overhead for session tracking\n131: \n132: **Cons**:\n133: - Requires cookie support in client\n134: - Sticky sessions may cause uneven load\n135: \n136: **Decision**: Selected — provides the best balance of simplicity and functionality.\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### Option 2: JWT-Based Session Management\n141: \n142: **Approach**: Use JWT tokens containing session claims, validate at router level.\n143: \n144: **Pros**:\n145: - Stateless, no server-side storage needed\n146: - Built-in expiration\n147: - Cryptographically verified\n148: \n149: **Cons**:\n150: - Cannot revoke active sessions\n151: - Larger token size\n152: - More complex implementation\n153: \n154: **Decision**: Rejected — stateless nature prevents session management features like forced logout.\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Option 3: External Session Store (Redis)\n159: \n160: **Approach**: Store sessions in Redis for distributed access.\n161: \n162: **Pros**:\n163: - Shared state across router instances\n164: - Persistence beyond process lifetime\n165: \n166: **Cons**:\n167: - Adds external dependency\n168: - Network latency for session operations\n169: - Additional infrastructure requirement\n170: \n171: **Decision**: Rejected — adds complexity; in-memory store suffices for single-instance deployment.\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ### Option 4: Client-Side Session (URL Rewriting)\n176: \n177: **Approach**: Encode session ID in URL paths.\n178: \n179: **Pros**:\n180: - Works without cookies\n181: \n182: **Cons**:\n183: - URL pollution\n184: - Security concerns\n185: - Not suitable for REST APIs\n186: \n187: **Decision**: Rejected — not appropriate for API-focused routing.\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ## Implementation Plan\n192: \n193: ### Phase 1: Session Core\n194: - [ ] Define Session struct with ID, UserID, Backend, StartTime, LastActivity, Metadata\n195: - [ ] Implement SessionStore interface with thread-safe operations\n196: - [ ] Implement in-memory SessionStore with map and RWMutex\n197: - [ ] Add session ID generation (UUID v4)\n198: \n199: ### Phase 2: Session Middleware\n200: - [ ] Extract session ID from cookie or X-Session-ID header\n201: - [ ] Create new session if not exists (when SessionEnabled)\n202: - [ ] Inject session cookie in response\n203: - [ ] Update last activity on each request\n204: \n205: ### Phase 3: Session Affinity\n206: - [ ] Modify RouteHandler to check session affinity\n207: - [ ] Store backend key in session\n208: - [ ] Route to stored backend when session exists\n209: - [ ] Handle backend removal with session invalidation\n210: \n211: ### Phase 4: Session Lifecycle\n212: - [ ] Implement session expiration checking\n213: - [ ] Add background goroutine for cleanup\n214: - [ ] Handle session deletion on backend removal\n215: - [ ] Add configuration for timeout and limits\n216: \n217: ### Phase 5: Metrics and Observability\n218: - [ ] Add session counter (active, created, expired)\n219: - [ ] Add session rate metrics\n220: - [ ] Add session duration histogram\n221: - [ ] Export session metrics to Prometheus\n222: \n223: ### Phase 6: Testing\n224: - [ ] Unit tests for SessionStore operations\n225: - [ ] Unit tests for session middleware\n226: - [ ] Unit tests for session affinity\n227: - [ ] Mock tests for session lifecycle\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ## Acceptance Criteria\n232: \n233: - [ ] Session store supports create, get, update, delete operations\n234: - [ ] Session ID is generated as UUID v4\n235: - [ ] Session cookie is set on first request when enabled\n236: - [ ] Subsequent requests with same cookie route to same backend\n237: - [ ] Sessions expire after configured timeout\n238: - [ ] Expired sessions are cleaned up automatically\n239: - [ ] Session metrics are exported (active_sessions, session_created_total, session_expired_total)\n240: - [ ] Max session limit is enforced\n241: - [ ] Session data includes user ID, backend, start time, last activity\n242: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >70% coverage\n243: - [ ] Graceful shutdown closes session store\n\n(End of file - total 243 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement session management capabilities in `pkg/router` to track, manage, and persist user sessions when routing to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends. This enables sticky sessions, session affinity, session lifecycle management, and provides operational visibility into active sessions.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AR-009 router implements HTTP reverse proxying to dynamically route requests to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter sandboxes. Currently:\n\n- **No session tracking**: Requests are routed without awareness of session context\n- **No sticky sessions**: Load balancing distributes requests across backends without session affinity\n- **No session lifecycle**: No mechanism to track when sessions start/end\n- **No session state visibility**: No way to query active sessions or session metadata\n\n### Goal\n\nProvide session management that:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775849283204,"end":1775849283237}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849283252,"sessionID":"ses_28722a5a2ffeY5t3bH1W5LyxEo","part":{"id":"prt_d78dd8f6e0018xSunOguATONno","messageID":"msg_d78dd84da001BVFahffAoIlBAA","sessionID":"ses_28722a5a2ffeY5t3bH1W5LyxEo","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4e1100fbba684c9c88ab7e86","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/auth.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/auth.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"net/http\"\n5: \t\"strings\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: type Authenticator struct {\n9: \ttoken   string\n10: \tenabled bool\n11: }\n12: \n13: func NewAuthenticator(token string, enabled bool) *Authenticator {\n14: \treturn &Authenticator{\n15: \t\ttoken:   token,\n16: \t\tenabled: enabled,\n17: \t}\n18: }\n19: \n20: func (a *Authenticator) Middleware(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n21: \treturn http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n22: \t\tif !a.enabled {\n23: \t\t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n24: \t\t\treturn\n25: \t\t}\n26: \n27: \t\tauthHeader := r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\")\n28: \t\tif authHeader == \"\" {\n29: \t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"Unauthorized\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n30: \t\t\treturn\n31: \t\t}\n32: \n33: \t\tparts := strings.SplitN(authHeader, \" \", 2)\n34: \t\tif len(parts) != 2 || strings.ToLower(parts[0]) != \"bearer\" {\n35: \t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"Unauthorized\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n36: \t\t\treturn\n37: \t\t}\n38: \n39: \t\tif parts[1] != a.token {\n40: \t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"Unauthorized\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n41: \t\t\treturn\n42: \t\t}\n43: \n44: \t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n45: \t})\n46: }\n47: \n48: func (a *Authenticator) IsEnabled() bool {\n49: \treturn a.enabled\n50: }\n51: \n52: func (a *Authenticator) SetToken(token string) {\n53: \ta.token = token\n54: }\n55: \n56: func (a *Authenticator) Enable() {\n57: \ta.enabled = true\n58: }\n59: \n60: func (a *Authenticator) Disable() {\n61: \ta.enabled = false\n62: }\n\n(End of file - total 62 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"strings\"\n)\n\ntype Authenticator struct {\n\ttoken   string\n\tenabled bool\n}\n\nfunc NewAuthenticator(token string, enabled bool) *Authenticator {\n\treturn &Authenticator{\n\t\ttoken:   token,\n\t\tenabled: enabled,\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (a *Authenticator) Middleware(next http.Handler) http.Handler {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/auth.go","time":{"start":1775849283196,"end":1775849283251}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849283256,"sessionID":"ses_28722a5a2ffeY5t3bH1W5LyxEo","part":{"id":"prt_d78dd9478001X6IiopjCVVbJc8","messageID":"msg_d78dd84da001BVFahffAoIlBAA","sessionID":"ses_28722a5a2ffeY5t3bH1W5LyxEo","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e6f41d469e734073a359f2be","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/session.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/session.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"errors\"\n5: \t\"sync\"\n6: \t\"time\"\n7: \n8: \t\"github.com/google/uuid\"\n9: )\n10: \n11: var (\n12: \tErrMaxSessionsExceeded = errors.New(\"maximum number of sessions exceeded\")\n13: \tErrSessionNotFound     = errors.New(\"session not found\")\n14: )\n15: \n16: type Session struct {\n17: \tID           string            // Unique session identifier\n18: \tBackendKey   string            // Associated backend key for sticky sessions\n19: \tCreatedAt    time.Time         // Session creation time\n20: \tLastActivity time.Time         // Last activity timestamp\n21: \tExpiresAt    time.Time         // Session expiration time\n22: \tMetadata     map[string]string // Additional session metadata\n23: }\n24: \n25: type SessionStore interface {\n26: \tCreate(backendKey string, metadata map[string]string) (*Session, error)\n27: \tGet(sessionID string) *Session\n28: \tUpdate(sessionID string) error\n29: \tDelete(sessionID string) error\n30: \tList() []*Session\n31: \tCleanup() int\n32: \tGetActiveCount() int\n33: \tSetMaxSessions(max int)\n34: }\n35: \n36: type MemorySessionStore struct {\n37: \tsessions       map[string]*Session\n38: \tmaxSessions    int\n39: \tsessionTimeout time.Duration\n40: \tmu             sync.RWMutex\n41: }\n42: \n43: func NewMemorySessionStore(maxSessions int) *MemorySessionStore {\n44: \tif maxSessions <= 0 {\n45: \t\tmaxSessions = 10000\n46: \t}\n47: \treturn &MemorySessionStore{\n48: \t\tsessions:       make(map[string]*Session),\n49: \t\tmaxSessions:    maxSessions,\n50: \t\tsessionTimeout: 30 * time.Minute,\n51: \t}\n52: }\n53: \n54: func NewMemorySessionStoreWithTimeout(maxSessions int, timeout time.Duration) *MemorySessionStore {\n55: \tif maxSessions <= 0 {\n56: \t\tmaxSessions = 10000\n57: \t}\n58: \tif timeout <= 0 {\n59: \t\ttimeout = 30 * time.Minute\n60: \t}\n61: \treturn &MemorySessionStore{\n62: \t\tsessions:       make(map[string]*Session),\n63: \t\tmaxSessions:    maxSessions,\n64: \t\tsessionTimeout: timeout,\n65: \t}\n66: }\n67: \n68: func GenerateSessionID() string {\n69: \treturn uuid.New().String()\n70: }\n71: \n72: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) Create(backendKey string, metadata map[string]string) (*Session, error) {\n73: \tms.mu.Lock()\n74: \tdefer ms.mu.Unlock()\n75: \n76: \tif len(ms.sessions) >= ms.maxSessions {\n77: \t\treturn nil, ErrMaxSessionsExceeded\n78: \t}\n79: \n80: \tnow := time.Now()\n81: \tsession := &Session{\n82: \t\tID:           GenerateSessionID(),\n83: \t\tBackendKey:   backendKey,\n84: \t\tCreatedAt:    now,\n85: \t\tLastActivity: now,\n86: \t\tExpiresAt:    now.Add(ms.sessionTimeout),\n87: \t\tMetadata:     metadata,\n88: \t}\n89: \n90: \tms.sessions[session.ID] = session\n91: \treturn session, nil\n92: }\n93: \n94: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) Get(sessionID string) *Session {\n95: \tms.mu.RLock()\n96: \tdefer ms.mu.RUnlock()\n97: \n98: \tsession, exists := ms.sessions[sessionID]\n99: \tif !exists {\n100: \t\treturn nil\n101: \t}\n102: \n103: \tif time.Now().After(session.ExpiresAt) {\n104: \t\treturn nil\n105: \t}\n106: \n107: \treturn session\n108: }\n109: \n110: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) Update(sessionID string) error {\n111: \tms.mu.Lock()\n112: \tdefer ms.mu.Unlock()\n113: \n114: \tsession, exists := ms.sessions[sessionID]\n115: \tif !exists {\n116: \t\treturn ErrSessionNotFound\n117: \t}\n118: \n119: \tsession.LastActivity = time.Now()\n120: \tsession.ExpiresAt = time.Now().Add(ms.sessionTimeout)\n121: \treturn nil\n122: }\n123: \n124: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) Delete(sessionID string) error {\n125: \tms.mu.Lock()\n126: \tdefer ms.mu.Unlock()\n127: \n128: \tif _, exists := ms.sessions[sessionID]; !exists {\n129: \t\treturn ErrSessionNotFound\n130: \t}\n131: \n132: \tdelete(ms.sessions, sessionID)\n133: \treturn nil\n134: }\n135: \n136: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) List() []*Session {\n137: \tms.mu.RLock()\n138: \tdefer ms.mu.RUnlock()\n139: \n140: \tsessions := make([]*Session, 0, len(ms.sessions))\n141: \tfor _, session := range ms.sessions {\n142: \t\tif time.Now().Before(session.ExpiresAt) {\n143: \t\t\tsessions = append(sessions, session)\n144: \t\t}\n145: \t}\n146: \n147: \treturn sessions\n148: }\n149: \n150: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) Cleanup() int {\n151: \tms.mu.Lock()\n152: \tdefer ms.mu.Unlock()\n153: \n154: \tnow := time.Now()\n155: \tcleaned := 0\n156: \n157: \tfor id, session := range ms.sessions {\n158: \t\tif now.After(session.ExpiresAt) {\n159: \t\t\tdelete(ms.sessions, id)\n160: \t\t\tcleaned++\n161: \t\t}\n162: \t}\n163: \n164: \treturn cleaned\n165: }\n166: \n167: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) GetActiveCount() int {\n168: \tms.mu.RLock()\n169: \tdefer ms.mu.RUnlock()\n170: \n171: \tcount := 0\n172: \tnow := time.Now()\n173: \tfor _, session := range ms.sessions {\n174: \t\tif now.Before(session.ExpiresAt) {\n175: \t\t\tcount++\n176: \t\t}\n177: \t}\n178: \n179: \treturn count\n180: }\n181: \n182: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) SetMaxSessions(max int) {\n183: \tms.mu.Lock()\n184: \tdefer ms.mu.Unlock()\n185: \n186: \tms.maxSessions = max\n187: }\n188: \n189: func (ms *MemorySessionStore) InvalidateBackend(backendKey string) int {\n190: \tms.mu.Lock()\n191: \tdefer ms.mu.Unlock()\n192: \n193: \tcleaned := 0\n194: \tfor id, session := range ms.sessions {\n195: \t\tif session.BackendKey == backendKey {\n196: \t\t\tdelete(ms.sessions, id)\n197: \t\t\tcleaned++\n198: \t\t}\n199: \t}\n200: \n201: \treturn cleaned\n202: }\n\n(End of file - total 202 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/google/uuid\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tErrMaxSessionsExceeded = errors.New(\"maximum number of sessions exceeded\")\n\tErrSessionNotFound     = errors.New(\"session not found\")\n)\n\ntype Session struct {\n\tID           string            // Unique session identifier\n\tBackendKey   string            // Associated backend key for sticky sessions\n\tCreatedAt    time.Time         // Session creation time\n\tLastActivity time.Time         // Last activity timestamp","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/session.go","time":{"start":1775849283200,"end":1775849283253}}}}
